  <mads:note type="source">Happ, H. Luxurius, 1986: v. 1-2, t.p. (Luxurius) v. 1, p. 83, etc. (lived in Carthage at time Vandals ruled; Roman according to
        general opinion; wrote most of his epigrams 523-530, a few 530-534; name also written Luxorius; may be same as person named Lisorius)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">LC manual cat. (hdg.: Luxorius, 6th cent.)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Oxford class. dict., 1970 (Luxorius of Carthage, early 6th c. A.D.; grammarian and poet)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Harper's dict. of class. lit. and antiq., 1937 (Luxorius; also written Luxurius and Lusorius; Roman epigrammatic poet who lived in Africa
        about beginning of 6th cent. A.D.)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Kleine Pauly, v. 3, 1969 (Luxurius (Luxorius); Latin epigrammatist; lived in Carthage in 1st third of 6th cent.; cannot identify with
        poet named Lisorius)</mads:note>
